@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Galaxy Trucker Guide";
}

<style>
 h4, h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0;
}

ul, ol {
    margin-top: 0;
}
</style>

<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Setup</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Remove tiles if using expansions, same tiles for all flights</li>
                <li>Remove 25 tiles per player below max player count</li>
                <li>Exp 2: remove additional 25 tiles if <i>not</i> using Class IV ships</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Timer</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Begin timer in circle X where X = round number</li>
                <li>When timer runs out, any player can flip and move to next circle</li>
                <li>Only a player who is done building may flip timer to START circle</li>
                <li>All building stops when timer runs out in START circle</li>
                <li>Class IV flights: timer starts off board</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<!-- 5 Player Rules -->
<h3>Additional 5 player rules</h3>
<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>Cards such as Combat Zone and Sabotage will normally punish two players. But when there are only 2 players available (because of giving up or jumping to hyperspace) only one player is punished</li>
                <li>Two players get the 1st place finishing bonus</li>
                <li>1st and 2nd place get the bonus for best looking ship. If there is a tie for 2nd place, all 2nd-place players will get the bonus</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <ul>
                <li>If a reward is available to a limited number of players, one extra player can claim the reward, but its value is reduced by 1 credit or 1 block</li>
                <li>If a penalty affects only one player (the one with the lowest number) or a group of players (those who lost to a foe), the penalty applies also to the next player or group, but it is reduced by 1 (1 block, 1 flight day, 1 crew member, 1 blast of heavy cannon fire or 1 sabotage attempt)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<h3>Giving Up</h3>
<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0">After a card is fully resolved, give up if
                <ol>
                    <li>0 remaining awake humans OR</li>
                    <li>0 engine strength in open space OR</li>
                    <li>lapped by leader</li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <p style="margin-bottom: 0">If you gave up
                <ol>
                    <li>Remove rocket from board</li>
                    <li>No bonuses for finishing (order, nicest ship)</li>
                    <li>Sell goods at half price of total (round up)</li>
                    <li>Pay penalty for lost parts</li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<p>You may only choose to give up between adventure cards, not during the resolution.</p>

<hr />

<div class="table datatable">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <!-- Evil Machinations -->
            <h3>Evil Machinations</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Setup: give each player 4 cards</li>
                <li>Before building: each player secretly chooses 1 card</li>
                <li>Shuffle EM cards into middle 2 quarters of Adventure deck</li>
                <li>1 EM card on top of middle 2 quarters</li>
                <li>Loans
                    <ul>
                        <li>take loan token and $10</li>
                        <li>any time: return the loan token plus $12</li>
                        <li>if you cannot repay loan at end game, then you lose</li>
                        <li>must go into debt to pay penalties for lost tiles</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <!-- Rough Roads -->
            <h3>Rough Roads</h3>
            <p style="margin-top: 0">With Evil Machinations, players choose Evil Machinations cards <i>before</i> the Rough Roads cards are revealed</p>
            <p>Can use Rough Roads as a handicap for experienced players, but remove the Remorseless Fate card</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Pick a difficulty level X</li>
                <li>For each round, before building, draw X Rough Roads cards</li>
                <li>Discard those cards to box at end of round</li>
            </ul>


        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <!-- Support Team -->
            <h3>Support Team</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Round 1: no support team</li>
                <li>Round 2:
                    <ul>
                        <li>deal 3 to each player, choose 1</li>
                        <li>have access to ability A, but not B</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Round 3:
                    <ul>
                        <li>deal 2 to each player, choose 1</li>
                        <li>have access to both abilities for older support team</li>
                        <li>have access to ability A for newer team, but not B</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Round 4*:
                    <ul>
                        <li>deal 1 to each player</li>
                        <li>have access to both abilities for older support teams</li>
                        <li>have access to ability A for newer team, but not B</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Event Sequence</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Timer Starts "GO"
                    <br />
                    <span style="margin-left: 10px;">1a. DURING BULIDING</span>
                </li>
                <li>Timer Ends
                    <br />
                    <span style="margin-left: 10px;">2a. AFTER BUILDING</span>
                </li>
                <li>Place batteries and crew
                    <br />
                    <span style="margin-left: 10px;">3a. BEFORE THE FLIGHT</span>
                </li>
                <li>Begin revealing Adventure cards</li>
                <li>Finish Adventure cards
                    <br />
                    <span style="margin-left: 10px;">5a. AFTER THE FLIGHT or AT THE END OF THE FLIGHT</span>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

